Adding SimicsFS to a kernel source tree
=======================================

* Unpack the 'simicsfs-x.xx.tar.gz' file in the 'linux-2.4.x/fs/' directory.

* Rename Makefile_2.4 as Makefile

* Add the following lines to 'Makefile' and 'Config.in':

linux-2.4.x/fs/Makefile:
-----------------
subdir-$(CONFIG_SIMICSFS)       += simicsfs

linux-2.4.x/fs/Config.in:
------------------
tristate 'Simics hostfs' CONFIG_SIMICSFS

* Configure the Linux build, select simicsfs as module.

* Compile (and install) the kernel and its modules, or build the simicsfs
  module only using:

  $ cd linux-2.4.x
  $ make SUBDIRS=fs/simicsfs modules

* Install the resulting 'simicsfs.o' module file, and configure simicsfs as
  described in the Simics User Guide.
